Definition: an industrial process for making steel using a Bessemer converter to blast air through molten iron and thus burning the excess carbon and impurities
Example: the first successful method of making steel in quantity at low cost
Synonyms: industrial_process, steel_production, an, industrial, process, for, making, steel, using, a, Bessemer, converter, to, blast, air, through, molten, iron, and, thus, burning, the, excess, carbon, impurities, first, successful, method, of, in, quantity, at, low, cost
Category: noun.process
